---

# Economy

Players earn money after every completed investigation.

Money can be spent on:

Office upgrades

Hint purchases

Special office decorations

Achievement displays

Agency trophies

Advanced workstation themes

---

# Rewarded Ads

Players who don't want to spend real money can watch rewarded ads for:

Small cash bonuses

One investigation hint

Extra investigation attempts after failure

Daily bonus rewards

---

# In-App Purchases

Optional purchases include:

Cash bundles

Hint bundles

Premium office themes

Collector decorations

No purchase is required to complete the game.

Skill always matters more than spending.

---

# Offline First

The game is designed to work almost entirely offline.

Progress is stored locally on the player's device.

This keeps operating costs extremely low and allows the game to scale to millions of players without requiring expensive online infrastructure for core gameplay.

---

# The End Goal

By the end of the game, the player has gone from analyzing simple stolen backpacks to solving international conspiracies involving governments, corporations, intelligence agencies, organized crime, cyber warfare, and financial empires.

The player never becomes a superhero.

They become something far more dangerous:

**The person everyone depends on to find the truth.**

When the evidence doesn't make sense...

When investigators are confused...

When prosecutors are stuck...

When entire agencies disagree...

The file lands on one desk.

**Yours.**
